Lemon Bars — Michelin Pastry Standard
9 × 9 in / 23 × 23 cm pan · Yield: 16 precise portions

⸻

Objective
Crisp sablé base with clean snap; sharply lemon-forward curd, satin texture, just-set finish. Canadian measurements. Service-grade repeatability.

⸻

Ingredients

Shortbread Base
Unsalted butter, cold, cubed — 170 g (¾ cup)
Icing sugar — 70 g (½ cup)
All-purpose flour — 210 g (1¾ cups)
Fine sea salt — 2 g (¼ tsp)
Lemon zest, microplaned — from 1 lemon

Lemon Curd Layer
Large eggs — 4 (≈200 g without shells)
Granulated sugar — 250 g (1¼ cups)
Fresh lemon juice, strained — 180 mL (¾ cup)
Lemon zest, very fine — from 2 lemons
Heavy cream (35%) — 60 mL (¼ cup)
All-purpose flour — 30 g (¼ cup)
Fine sea salt — 1 g (⅛ tsp)

Finish (optional, restrained)
Icing sugar, sifted — minimal
Micro lemon zest or candied peel — minimal

⸻

Method

Shortbread Base
	1.	Heat oven to 175 °C. Line pan with parchment, leaving overhang.
	2.	Combine butter, icing sugar, salt, and zest. Mix just to homogeneity; no aeration.
	3.	Add flour. Mix until dough barely comes together.
	4.	Press evenly into pan; level. Dock lightly.
	5.	Bake 18–22 minutes until pale golden at edges. Keep warm.

Lemon Curd
	1.	Whisk sugar, flour, salt, and zest until evenly dispersed.
	2.	Add eggs and cream; whisk smooth.
	3.	Whisk in lemon juice last.
	4.	Pour gently over the hot base.
	5.	Bake at 165–170 °C for 20–25 minutes until centre is just set (slight wobble, no liquid).

Set
Cool completely at room temperature. Refrigerate minimum 3 hours before cutting.

⸻

Cutting & Service

Trim edges with a hot, dry knife. Cut into exact squares or narrow rectangles. Serve cold or lightly tempered. Garnish with one precise element only, if at all.

⸻

Technical Notes

• Flour stabilizes the curd without gelatin; clean lemon profile.
• Cream rounds acidity for a satin finish without muting brightness.
• Pouring onto a hot base prevents separation and ensures adhesion.
• Target doneness is just-set; overbaking dulls acidity and coarsens texture.
